|> You may have a problem if you want to triple encrypt DATA, as in a file.  I'm
|> not quite certain, but I think the NSA strongly frowns on using double length
                      ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
|> keys to encrypt data.  I think they only permit it for encrypting keys.  It's
|> sort of like the "exportable algorithm" issue - if your encryption method is
|> too strong, they don't want you using it to encrypt data, just keys.
|> 
|> Perhaps someone else can confirm this, since I don't completely trust my
